<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-29T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-29T14:00:00-05:00" n="853" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d853">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.711/2524</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-29T15:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>8508. Your despatch 9275, June 7. Before Department determines its
                            attitude towards British decision regarding censorship of foreign
                            diplomatic correspondence in transit through England, please report
                            present system of transit of American pouches and whether carried by
                            couriers from arriving to departing steamers or entrusted to British
                            postal administration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>